---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Financial AI Workflow Control | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing financial systems to enforce deterministic policy checks before model execution in AML, KYC, fraud, dispute review, and customer-impacting workflows."
>
  <section class="stack-section">
    <h1>Deterministic control for AI-assisted financial workflows.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard deploys alongside existing financial applications as an inline policy proxy. It enforces policy checks before model execution in AML, KYC, fraud, dispute review, and customer-impacting workflow paths.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Existing Financial Systems Remain in Place</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not substitute for transactional AML, KYC, fraud, dispute, ledger, or internal case-management systems. It secures existing financial workflow pipelines by providing an inline enforcement checkpoint that evaluates AI-bound requests against deterministic policy schemas before model execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Financial Use Cases</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>AML analyst review</li>
      <li>KYC escalation support</li>
      <li>Fraud exception handling</li>
      <li>Dispute resolution assistance</li>
      <li>Account action or customer-impacting recommendation gating</li>
      <li>Cross-border transfer review support</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>Fintech Control Points</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Analyst workflow authorization</li>
      <li>Required structured context validation</li>
      <li>Transaction or case metadata validation</li>
      <li>Source-system trust validation</li>
      <li>Replay/freshness checks</li>
      <li>Policy-based allow/deny/review routing</li>
      <li>Evidence for security, risk, compliance, and audit review</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="stack-section">
    <h2>What BeaconGuard Does Not Replace</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard does not replace AML case management, fraud decisioning, transaction monitoring, KYC systems, SIEM, model monitoring, or legal compliance review. BeaconGuard is the runtime control and evidence layer at the AI request boundary.
    </p>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="mailto:architecture@beaconguardassurance.com?subject=Financial%20Workflow%20Review">Request a Financial Workflow Review</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
